about.summary: A tool that "multiply imputes" missing data in a single cross-section (such as a survey), from a time series (like variables collected for each year in a country), or from a time-series-cross-sectional data set (such as collected by years for each of several countries). Amelia II implements our bootstrapping-based algorithm that gives essentially the same answers as the standard IP or EMis approaches, is usually considerably faster than existing approaches and can handle many more variables.  Unlike Amelia I and other statistically rigorous imputation software, it virtually never crashes (but please let us know if you find to the contrary!).  The program also generalizes existing approaches by allowing for trends in time series across observations within a cross-sectional unit, as well as priors that allow experts to incorporate beliefs they have about the values of missing cells in their data.  Amelia II also includes useful diagnostics of the fit of multiple imputation models.  The program works from the R command line or via a graphical user interface that does not require users to know R.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.7.6' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-amelia
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Amelia_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/Amelia/Amelia_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 63c08d374aaf78af46c34dc78da719b3085e58d9fabdc76c6460d5193a621bea

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - libopenblas
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.11
    - r-rcpparmadillo
    - r-foreign
  run:
    - libopenblas
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.11
    - r-rcpparmadillo
    - r-foreign

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('Amelia')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('Amelia')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://gking.harvard.edu/amelia
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: A tool that "multiply imputes" missing data in a single cross-section (such as a survey),

    users to know R.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
